Well, I don't know, he was always a Liberal but that's all I ever remember - I remember he was always a Liberal but he never took no active part in nothing of that, only just voting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8985554 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7996314\charrsid7502071 Why do you think he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12390326 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7996314\charrsid7502071 
Well that was - you could always - always knew that when the polling come along and - they always - well, they - they used to have to come to Thorpe to vote you see, all round from Beaumont and all like that
 - all those villages used to come to Thorpe to the poll. They used to come in farm wagons and all things like that. Well, nine times of ten they'd get fighting. The Conservatives and - Liberals. Oh yes. And of course father always had his yellow rosette,
 so they knew he was Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8985554 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7996314\charrsid7502071 Did he get mixed up in a fight too?
